Two people were found injured in a crashed vehicle after it was alleged that they were hijacked by an armed gang near Port Shepstone and fled when they lost control of the vehicle in the vicinity of Bizana, on Monday night. According to KZN Private Ambulance spokesperson, Craig Botha, when KwaZulu Private Ambulance Service responded to the R61 between Port Edward and Bizana they found that a vehicle had lost control and left the road. “Paramedics quickly assessed the scene and found that one patient sustained serious injuries and one other patient sustained minor injuries. The patients were treated on scene before being transported to hospital for further treatment,” said Botha. He added that according to the occupants from the car, they stated that they had been hijacked by four armed suspects near Port Shepstone and were being driven towards Bizana when the suspects lost control of the vehicle and crashed. “The suspects fled the scene leaving the injured occupants in the vehicle,” Botha added.